item.title: How to remove an oversized object?
item.dc:creator: @badger41 badger41
item.description:
@badger41 wrote:

apparently, many arent aware that jagex, for a short period of time, made their models super large in size and then used the objectdef class to scale the model down to its normal size.

my suggestion: pack all 602 models and use the scale down feature, or dump the 317 stove model from another cache and pack it into yours.

inb4howidothat, im not giving you step by step instructions, you have a brain.

It’s a sign of model corruption. The scale is probably set to high in the cache (probably the result of packing models incorrectly).

I don’t know specifically how to fix it.
